Package edu.uiowa.cs.warp

Class Flow

java.lang.Object
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.SchedulableObject
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.Flow
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Flow>
public class Flow extends edu.uiowa.cs.warp.SchedulableObject implements Comparable<Flow>

This class is for representing network flows. Network flows are used to model the communication patterns between other flows within the network. Each flow has the following properties: priority, index, and values that show if data has been transmitted reliably. Flows are compared based off their priority and contain nodes and edges

Author:
sgoddard, Frank Forliano (creating comments, for JavaDoc)
